    "synopsis": "Lured deep into the Signus Cluster by what looks like an Imperial system gone silent, Sanguinius brings the Blood Angels in expecting a routine Compliance and finds Horus's first deliberate move against his most trusted brother. The cluster has been remade as a warp anchor by Word Bearers ritualists; daemons of Khorne and Slaanesh boil out of the planets, and the Bloodthirster Ka'Bandha hunts the Ninth Legion for a personal reckoning with their primarch. First Captain Raldoron holds the line on the surface while Apothecary Meros wrestles with the Red Thirst stirring through his battle-brothers, and Sanguinius — knowing now that the Warmaster has bait-and-trapped him — turns Signus from grave into proof that the Blood Angels will not break.",
